So imagine this scenario: I have my IDE open and I have been using CLaude Code for some time, the Extension's status bar shows "36.4K - X% - Cache 4m - Reset in 3h12", and I decide to shut down my IDE because of an update for Cursor, when I reopen the IDE and the same project and continue working with CLaude Code, the extension will load up again as well the moment I start talking to Claude Code again, but it will show "0k - 0% - Cache: 4m - Reset in 4h59m", why does our extension do a complete reset to default values? Shouldn't it have remembered the previous tokens I had used in my previous chat with Claude Code before closing and reopening my IDE and Claude Code? 